564
00:21:19,570 --> 00:21:21,770
one of the places his hosts took him to

565
00:21:21,770 --> 00:21:23,150
was the House of Commons

566
00:21:23,710 --> 00:21:25,570
and this he tries to explain

567
00:21:25,570 --> 00:21:27,230
to his readers back home.

568
00:21:27,770 --> 00:21:29,730
He begins with a rather unflattering comparison.

569
00:21:30,110 --> 00:21:31,590
He describes the two sides

570
00:21:31,590 --> 00:21:33,610
of the house and says this

571
00:21:33,610 --> 00:21:35,810
is like what one often sees in India

572
00:21:35,810 --> 00:21:37,170
two trees

573
00:21:37,170 --> 00:21:39,730
on opposite sides of the road both full of

574
00:21:39,730 --> 00:21:41,550
parrots squawking at each other.

575
00:21:43,250 --> 00:21:45,790
But then he goes on to explain what this is for

576
00:21:45,790 --> 00:21:47,590
and he explains that

577
00:21:47,590 --> 00:21:49,550
the poor benighted English

578
00:21:49,550 --> 00:21:51,730
unlike the Muslims had never

579
00:21:51,730 --> 00:21:53,230
accepted a divine law

580
00:21:53,230 --> 00:21:56,030
and were therefore reduced to the expedient

581
00:21:56,030 --> 00:21:57,510
of making their own laws

582
00:21:57,510 --> 00:21:59,670
in accordance with the experience

583
00:21:59,670 --> 00:22:01,710
of their judges and the necessities

584
00:22:01,710 --> 00:22:03,690
of the moment, which he regards

585
00:22:03,690 --> 00:22:05,590
obviously as a very

586
00:22:06,350 --> 00:22:08,010
poor expedient

587
00:22:08,010 --> 00:22:08,850
the people

588
00:22:09,480 --> 00:22:11,210
who have denied themselves

589
00:22:11,210 --> 00:22:13,870
this major benefit of divine

590
00:22:13,870 --> 00:22:14,490
guidance.

591
00:22:15,490 --> 00:22:17,890
That system you don't need

592
00:22:17,890 --> 00:22:19,230
a legislative assembly

593
00:22:19,970 --> 00:22:21,410
and that of course

594
00:22:21,410 --> 00:22:22,820
has far reaching implications.

595
00:22:24,970 --> 00:22:27,010
Another factor against linked to this

596
00:22:27,010 --> 00:22:28,450
is the triumphalism.

597
00:22:28,850 --> 00:22:31,030
The belief which Islam shares

598
00:22:31,030 --> 00:22:33,030
with Christianity and as far as I know

599
00:22:33,030 --> 00:22:34,210
with no other religion

600
00:22:34,210 --> 00:22:36,620
are being the final possessor

601
00:22:37,210 --> 00:22:38,330
of God's truth

602
00:22:38,330 --> 00:22:40,870
which it is therefore their

603
00:22:40,870 --> 00:22:42,970
sacred duty to bring to others.

604
00:22:42,970 --> 00:22:45,350
This again makes

605
00:22:46,150 --> 00:22:47,410
the interchange

606
00:22:47,410 --> 00:22:48,970
and exchange

607
00:22:48,970 --> 00:22:51,410
of democratic life more difficult.

608
00:22:52,850 --> 00:22:54,970
One of the most serious

609
00:22:56,290 --> 00:22:56,930
obstructions

610
00:22:56,930 --> 00:22:59,010
is the position of women.

611
00:23:01,750 --> 00:23:03,330
The first who raised this as a

612
00:23:03,330 --> 00:23:04,990
major issue as far as I am aware

613
00:23:04,990 --> 00:23:07,170
in a Muslim country was

614
00:23:07,170 --> 00:23:09,090
Kamal Atatürk who again has

615
00:23:09,090 --> 00:23:10,950
been mentioned several times at these

616
00:23:10,950 --> 00:23:12,930
meetings, the founder

617
00:23:12,930 --> 00:23:14,270
and first president

618
00:23:14,850 --> 00:23:16,190
of the Turkish Republic,

619
00:23:17,250 --> 00:23:18,870
an Ottoman Pasha and a military

620
00:23:18,870 --> 00:23:20,830
general, an improbable feminist.

621
00:23:22,170 --> 00:23:22,770
Nevertheless

622
00:23:22,770 --> 00:23:24,910
he was the first to

623
00:23:24,910 --> 00:23:27,210
proclaim the need for the emancipation

624
00:23:27,210 --> 00:23:29,290
of women and the giving of political

625
00:23:29,290 --> 00:23:30,490
rights to women.

626
00:23:31,730 --> 00:23:32,250
He said

627
00:23:32,850 --> 00:23:34,990
several times in a series of speeches

628
00:23:34,990 --> 00:23:36,990
which he delivered in Anatolia in the early

629
00:23:37,890 --> 00:23:38,950
1920s, he said

630
00:23:38,950 --> 00:23:40,050
that our present task

631
00:23:40,050 --> 00:23:42,190
is to catch up with the modern world.

632
00:23:42,990 --> 00:23:44,610
We will not catch up with the modern

633
00:23:44,610 --> 00:23:46,810
world if we only modernize half

634
00:23:46,810 --> 00:23:47,710
the population.

635
00:23:49,430 --> 00:23:50,570
A point which he understood

636
00:23:50,570 --> 00:23:52,710
which many others still have

637
00:23:52,710 --> 00:23:54,710
difficulty in understanding.

638
00:23:55,910 --> 00:23:56,930
If we look at

639
00:23:56,930 --> 00:23:58,910
the accounts of the West

640
00:23:58,910 --> 00:24:00,490
written by Muslim travelers

641
00:24:01,390 --> 00:24:03,090
this is the point on which

642
00:24:03,650 --> 00:24:04,870
almost all seem

643
00:24:04,870 --> 00:24:06,930
to agree the astonishing

644
00:24:06,930 --> 00:24:08,670
to them freedom

645
00:24:08,670 --> 00:24:10,570
accorded to women in Western

646
00:24:10,570 --> 00:24:12,190
and Christian society.

647
00:24:13,390 --> 00:24:14,810
Obviously the position of women

648
00:24:14,810 --> 00:24:16,930
was very far from one of equality in the

649
00:24:16,930 --> 00:24:18,790
West but it was incomparably

650
00:24:18,790 --> 00:24:20,790
better than in most other parts of the world.

651
00:24:21,350 --> 00:24:22,750
One that I find particularly

652
00:24:24,190 --> 00:24:24,710
instructive

653
00:24:24,710 --> 00:24:26,930
is a report from a Moroccan ambassador

654
00:24:26,930 --> 00:24:28,670
in Spain in the late

655
00:24:28,670 --> 00:24:31,010
17th century who comments

656
00:24:31,010 --> 00:24:33,010
on the free and easy ways

657
00:24:33,010 --> 00:24:35,010
of Spanish ladies and the lack

658
00:24:35,010 --> 00:24:37,110
of manly jealousy of Spanish men.

659
00:24:37,890 --> 00:24:38,870
This is Spain

660
00:24:38,870 --> 00:24:41,270
of all places in the late

661
00:24:41,270 --> 00:24:42,210
17th century.

662
00:24:43,170 --> 00:24:45,030
His report on Spain doesn't tell us much

663
00:24:45,030 --> 00:24:46,930
about Spain but he tells us quite a lot about

664
00:24:46,930 --> 00:24:47,330
Morocco.

665
00:24:50,970 --> 00:24:52,770
One of the major reasons

666
00:24:52,770 --> 00:24:55,130
for the relative backwardness of

667
00:24:55,130 --> 00:24:57,150
Islam is surely this

668
00:24:57,150 --> 00:24:59,570
point. If a society

669
00:24:59,570 --> 00:25:00,750
persists

670
00:25:00,750 --> 00:25:03,130
in depriving itself of

671
00:25:03,130 --> 00:25:05,450
the talents and services of half the population

672
00:25:05,450 --> 00:25:07,190
and of entrusting

673
00:25:07,190 --> 00:25:08,850
the nurture of the other half

674
00:25:08,850 --> 00:25:11,210
to uneducated and down trodden

675
00:25:11,210 --> 00:25:13,110
mothers, it will not be able

676
00:25:13,110 --> 00:25:14,690
to keep up with the modern world

677
00:25:14,690 --> 00:25:17,350
nor will it be able to operate any

678
00:25:17,350 --> 00:25:18,930
kind of free

679
00:25:18,930 --> 00:25:20,870
liberal democratic society.

680
00:25:21,650 --> 00:25:23,130
This is increasingly understood

681
00:25:25,270 --> 00:25:26,350
not always

682
00:25:27,090 --> 00:25:29,310
not only I should say

683
00:25:29,310 --> 00:25:31,550
by women, there are there as elsewhere

684
00:25:31,550 --> 00:25:33,550
some women who prefer subordination

685
00:25:34,470 --> 00:25:35,830
but I feel

686
00:25:35,830 --> 00:25:37,690
myself that women who are

687
00:25:37,690 --> 00:25:40,030
after all slightly more than half the population

688
00:25:40,030 --> 00:25:41,570
may yet constitute

689
00:25:41,570 --> 00:25:43,450
the best hope for liberal democracy

690
00:25:43,450 --> 00:25:45,230
in the Islamic world.

691
00:25:47,350 --> 00:25:49,830
I have already mentioned the lack of a legislative

692
00:25:49,830 --> 00:25:51,550
power and therefore the

693
00:25:52,350 --> 00:25:53,490
absence of any need

694
00:25:53,490 --> 00:25:55,070
for a legislative assembly.

695
00:25:58,970 --> 00:25:59,850
One could add

696
00:25:59,850 --> 00:26:01,810
to that the difficulties

697
00:26:02,930 --> 00:26:04,430
arising, this may seem

698
00:26:04,430 --> 00:26:06,170
to you an odd formulation but I stand

699
00:26:06,170 --> 00:26:07,910
by it, difficulties arising

700
00:26:07,910 --> 00:26:09,790
at the present time from oil.

701
00:26:11,170 --> 00:26:12,150
Oil has

702
00:26:12,150 --> 00:26:14,350
enormously enriched some

703
00:26:14,350 --> 00:26:15,710
Muslim governments.

704
00:26:16,810 --> 00:26:17,990
It has freed them

705
00:26:17,990 --> 00:26:20,310
from the need to raise taxes.

706
00:26:21,610 --> 00:26:22,170
It has

707
00:26:22,170 --> 00:26:23,870
freed them therefore from the need

708
00:26:23,870 --> 00:26:26,190
to enter into a dialogue with their subjects.

709
00:26:27,110 --> 00:26:28,150
It has provided

710
00:26:28,150 --> 00:26:30,390
resources to maintain tyranny

711
00:26:30,390 --> 00:26:32,050
at home and terrorism abroad

712
00:26:32,050 --> 00:26:34,450
and in the long run it may well

713
00:26:34,450 --> 00:26:35,950
prove to be a great curse

714
00:26:35,950 --> 00:26:37,470
rather than a blessing.

715
00:26:38,090 --> 00:26:40,130
And it is surely not without

716
00:26:40,130 --> 00:26:42,370
significance that the most hopeful

717
00:26:42,370 --> 00:26:44,010
signs of development

718
00:26:44,010 --> 00:26:45,830
towards a freer society

719
00:26:45,830 --> 00:26:48,250
occur in countries like

720
00:26:48,250 --> 00:26:50,130
Tunisia and Jordan

721
00:26:51,150 --> 00:26:52,530
and Turkey

722
00:26:52,530 --> 00:26:54,010
which have no oil.

723
00:26:56,770 --> 00:26:58,130
Another difficulty

724
00:26:58,130 --> 00:26:59,790
is the absence in

725
00:26:59,790 --> 00:27:01,830
Muslim law of what in

726
00:27:01,830 --> 00:27:03,650
Roman law is called the legal

727
00:27:03,650 --> 00:27:04,270
person.

728
00:27:05,230 --> 00:27:06,390
There are only individuals.

729
00:27:06,570 --> 00:27:08,910
There is no city, just an accumulation

730
00:27:08,910 --> 00:27:10,210
of quarters and houses.

731
00:27:10,730 --> 00:27:12,490
There is no abstract

732
00:27:12,490 --> 00:27:14,810
legal, no corporate legal

733
00:27:14,810 --> 00:27:15,310
entity.

734
00:27:15,950 --> 00:27:17,650
This is an alien notion.

735
00:27:18,970 --> 00:27:20,370
Therefore no form

736
00:27:20,370 --> 00:27:22,590
of representation, no

737
00:27:22,590 --> 00:27:24,330
form of majority decision.

738
00:27:24,930 --> 00:27:26,650
In the past this didn't matter

739
00:27:26,650 --> 00:27:29,090
but in trying to create

740
00:27:29,090 --> 00:27:30,590
liberal democratic

741
00:27:30,590 --> 00:27:32,750
institutions the absence

742
00:27:32,750 --> 00:27:34,590
of such a tradition is

743
00:27:34,590 --> 00:27:36,230
a serious obstacle.

744
00:27:37,110 --> 00:27:38,570
It's an obstacle which is now

745
00:27:38,570 --> 00:27:40,170
increasingly being overcome

746
00:27:40,170 --> 00:27:42,570
as the modern economy

747
00:27:42,570 --> 00:27:44,710
has created the need for

748
00:27:44,710 --> 00:27:46,550
such institutions and such

749
00:27:46,550 --> 00:27:47,030
laws.

750
00:27:49,010 --> 00:27:50,990
Let me turn now to

751
00:27:50,990 --> 00:27:52,750
what seem to me to be the factors

752
00:27:52,750 --> 00:27:54,990
in Islam which

753
00:27:54,990 --> 00:27:57,010
are conducive to the

754
00:27:57,010 --> 00:27:58,970
development of liberal

755
00:27:58,970 --> 00:27:59,610
democracy.

756
00:28:01,170 --> 00:28:03,190
The first and most important of these

757
00:28:03,770 --> 00:28:04,970
of the political

758
00:28:04,970 --> 00:28:07,050
factors is the

759
00:28:07,050 --> 00:28:08,450
Muslim doctrine of sovereignty.

760
00:28:09,150 --> 00:28:11,110
This is a subject which is

761
00:28:11,110 --> 00:28:12,530
widely discussed

762
00:28:15,290 --> 00:28:16,130
by

763
00:28:16,130 --> 00:28:17,070
jurists

764
00:28:17,070 --> 00:28:19,290
and theologians in Islam

765
00:28:19,290 --> 00:28:21,310
going back a very long way.

766
00:28:23,670 --> 00:28:24,950
And the

767
00:28:24,950 --> 00:28:25,590
supreme

768
00:28:25,590 --> 00:28:27,410
institution of sovereignty is the

769
00:28:27,410 --> 00:28:29,330
caliphate and there is much

770
00:28:29,330 --> 00:28:31,630
discussion as to how one becomes caliph

771
00:28:31,630 --> 00:28:33,170
and what one's duties are.

772
00:28:34,190 --> 00:28:35,450
And a reading of these

773
00:28:35,450 --> 00:28:36,850
texts makes it quite clear

774
00:28:36,850 --> 00:28:39,090
that according to Muslim doctrine

775
00:28:39,090 --> 00:28:41,350
the supreme sovereign office

776
00:28:42,730 --> 00:28:44,010
is contractual

777
00:28:44,010 --> 00:28:45,290
and consensual.

778
00:28:46,430 --> 00:28:47,490
The caliph becomes

779
00:28:47,490 --> 00:28:49,070
caliph by a contract

780
00:28:49,070 --> 00:28:50,810
between him and his subjects.

781
00:28:51,530 --> 00:28:53,710
A contract which imposes duties

782
00:28:53,710 --> 00:28:55,210
as well as giving

783
00:28:55,210 --> 00:28:57,270
rights to the ruler.

784
00:28:58,110 --> 00:28:59,750
And it is consensual

785
00:28:59,750 --> 00:29:01,450
in that it depends

786
00:29:01,450 --> 00:29:03,430
on the consent of the ruled.

787
00:29:04,190 --> 00:29:05,590
Now you might say this is

788
00:29:05,590 --> 00:29:07,690
theoretical, this isn't how it actually happened.

789
00:29:08,230 --> 00:29:09,530
This would be a

790
00:29:09,530 --> 00:29:11,430
valid, though not entirely valid

791
00:29:11,430 --> 00:29:13,710
criticism. In that generally

792
00:29:13,710 --> 00:29:15,670
speaking certain minimal

793
00:29:15,670 --> 00:29:17,150
norms were observed.

794
00:29:17,930 --> 00:29:19,830
It is rare in Islamic history

795
00:29:19,830 --> 00:29:21,910
that you find a complete despotism.

796
00:29:22,530 --> 00:29:23,790
You find authoritarian

797
00:29:23,790 --> 00:29:25,750
rule certainly, but

798
00:29:25,750 --> 00:29:28,330
not unprincipled, unrestricted

799
00:29:28,330 --> 00:29:29,370
despotic rule.

800
00:29:29,830 --> 00:29:31,390
It is true that the law gives

801
00:29:31,390 --> 00:29:33,570
authoritarian, gives autocratic powers

802
00:29:33,570 --> 00:29:35,470
to the ruler, but it nevertheless

803
00:29:35,470 --> 00:29:37,270
defines those powers.

804
00:29:38,410 --> 00:29:39,890
An oft cited tradition

805
00:29:39,890 --> 00:29:41,710
of the prophet, as well as

806
00:29:41,710 --> 00:29:43,850
the Qur'an, Muslims believe in the traditions

807
00:29:43,850 --> 00:29:46,070
of the prophet, these are sayings of the prophet

808
00:29:46,070 --> 00:29:47,890
handed down by oral tradition.

809
00:29:48,610 --> 00:29:49,930
A much quoted tradition

810
00:29:49,930 --> 00:29:51,850
of the prophet is

811
00:29:51,850 --> 00:29:54,090
there is no obedience in sin.

812
00:29:55,090 --> 00:29:55,890
That means

813
00:29:55,890 --> 00:29:57,650
that the duty of obedience

814
00:29:57,650 --> 00:29:59,610
which the subject owes to the ruler

815
00:30:00,490 --> 00:30:01,910
lapses when the ruler

816
00:30:01,910 --> 00:30:04,050
orders something that is sinful.

817
00:30:04,830 --> 00:30:05,610
And in that case

818
00:30:05,610 --> 00:30:07,830
duty of obedience is replaced not

819
00:30:07,830 --> 00:30:09,770
by a right of disobedience as in western

820
00:30:09,770 --> 00:30:11,850
political thought, but by a duty

821
00:30:11,850 --> 00:30:12,930
of disobedience.

822
00:30:13,610 --> 00:30:16,290
Of course, there is no constitutional

823
00:30:16,290 --> 00:30:17,790
procedure to decide

824
00:30:17,790 --> 00:30:20,050
when a command is sinful.

825
00:30:20,830 --> 00:30:22,010
That is left to

826
00:30:22,010 --> 00:30:23,810
what we might tactfully call

827
00:30:23,810 --> 00:30:26,190
the play of historical forces.

828
00:30:27,790 --> 00:30:30,110
But the notion is there, the principle is there

829
00:30:30,110 --> 00:30:32,130
and it has increasingly been

830
00:30:32,130 --> 00:30:33,870
cited in modern times

831
00:30:33,870 --> 00:30:35,750
by Muslim dissidents

832
00:30:35,750 --> 00:30:36,910
of various kinds.

833
00:30:39,770 --> 00:30:40,890
Some reference

834
00:30:40,890 --> 00:30:42,310
was made this morning

835
00:30:42,310 --> 00:30:43,910
to tolerance.

836
00:30:44,910 --> 00:30:45,690
Professor Baudet

837
00:30:45,690 --> 00:30:47,130
spoke very rightly

838
00:30:47,130 --> 00:30:50,150
of the inadequacy of tolerance

839
00:30:50,150 --> 00:30:51,950
as a notion in our time.

840
00:30:53,070 --> 00:30:54,050
There is a letter

841
00:30:54,050 --> 00:30:55,150
of George Washington

842
00:30:55,150 --> 00:30:57,810
addressed to the leader of the Jewish community

843
00:30:57,810 --> 00:30:59,310
in Newport, Rhode Island,

844
00:30:59,770 --> 00:31:01,650
in which he says, I'm quoting from memory

845
00:31:01,650 --> 00:31:02,770
but I think accurately,

846
00:31:03,550 --> 00:31:05,130
he says, let us no longer speak of

847
00:31:05,130 --> 00:31:07,130
toleration as if it were

848
00:31:07,130 --> 00:31:09,550
by the indulgence of one group of people

849
00:31:09,550 --> 00:31:10,890
that others enjoy

850
00:31:10,890 --> 00:31:13,190
the exercise of their inherent

851
00:31:13,190 --> 00:31:14,430
natural rights.

852
00:31:16,930 --> 00:31:19,210
That is just over 200 years ago.

853
00:31:20,170 --> 00:31:21,310
It is still not

854
00:31:21,310 --> 00:31:22,190
generally accepted.

855
00:31:23,130 --> 00:31:25,370
In saying that though, I think we should bear in mind

856
00:31:25,370 --> 00:31:27,210
the very real tolerance

857
00:31:29,330 --> 00:31:31,030
exercised by Muslim governments

858
00:31:31,030 --> 00:31:33,290
